"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63207","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p>There have been no such discussions with the Secretary of State or other Defence Ministers.<br><br>It is our policy that Armed Forces personnel should be recruited to be fully fit for deployment worldwide on operations. For this reason, the Services do not recruit personnel with existing medical conditions which may adversely impact on the effectiveness of the Armed Forces, or which may themselves be exacerbated by military circumstances. <br><br>This is particularly relevant in cases of individuals with autism or Asperger's Syndrome, as military personnel are expected to perform in multiple roles, which may be difficult for someone suffering from these disorders. Further, all military personnel are required to work in close-knit teams, and in operational environments the pressures are such that anyone with significant disability in social interaction may potentially be a danger to themselves or their team. These two diagnoses have significant disability in social interaction as part of their defining features.<br><br>The policy on Asperger's has recently been changed to allow some minimal degree of relaxation for those candidates for the Services who do not display classic symptoms of the Syndrome or where their diagnosis may be in doubt. It places more emphasis on assessing their ability to perform as part of a team and to function within a simulated military environment and less on medical opinion.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-26T13:45:03.4415438Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63207/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63207/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Defence Consultant Adviser for Psychiatry about Asperger's syndrome in the context of the Defence Medical Services policy review; and whether he plans to change his Department's policy on the recruitment to the armed forces of people diagnosed with Asperger's syndrome.","false","Biography information for Jim Dobbin","Heywood and Middleton","Jim Dobbin","201860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63208","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-02","<p> </p><p>The Lightning II aircraft are being procured incrementally. To date the UK has ordered four F-35 B aircraft, three of which have been delivered. The approved cost for the production of the four aircraft, including initial spares provision, risk, concurrency, necessary programme and support arrangements, long lead items and our contribution to the composite share ratio for the next batch of aircraft is £999 million, as detailed in the National Audit Office Major Projects Report 2013.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-02T15:45:07.2319534Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63208/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63208/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63208/answer/previousversion/7467","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost is of each Lightning II his Department has ordered to date.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63209","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence has taken delivery of three aircraft to date. Two aircraft, ordered in Low Rate Initial Production (LRIP) 3, are at Block 1A software standard and one aircraft, ordered in LRIP 4, is at Block 2A standard.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201932","2014-07-01T15:42:41.2078023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63209/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63209/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, from which low-rate initial production lot each Lightning II delivered to his Department to date came from.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63210","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-01","<p>The Ministry of Defence has taken delivery of three aircraft to date. Two aircraft, ordered in Low Rate Initial Production (LRIP) 3, are at Block 1A software standard and one aircraft, ordered in LRIP 4, is at Block 2A standard.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201931","2014-07-01T15:42:41.0827489Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63210/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63210/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which software block is installed on each Lightning II delivered to his Department to date.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63211","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>As an initial planning assumption, the scheduled out of service date for the UK Lightning II fleet is 2048.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-30T15:10:38.2314658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63211/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63211/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the out of service date for the Lightning II.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63212","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The incremental nature of the F-35 approvals means that the total cost of the programme is updated after each Main Gate is endorsed. The UK F-35 programme is scheduled to seek financial approval for its fifth and final main gate in 2017. At this point the overall cost of the programme will be published. Whilst the Ministry of Defence maintains a detailed through-life cost estimate for the programme which forecasts all Main Gates it does not publish these figures ahead of formal contract negotiation.I am withholding the information as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-30T15:10:09.8899061Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63212/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63212/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the through life cost of the Lightning II project.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63213","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Lightning II aircraft is specifically designed to operate in a contested environment. Regular simulator work and operational analysis is carried out to confirm the system's performance and operational test of the aircraft is planned to do the same. The air system currently meets or exceeds our requirements. I am withholding the level of detail requested as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201936 ; 201971 ; 202105","2014-06-26T13:42:44.7741787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63213/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63213/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the Lightning II's combat capability against the (a) Chinese J-20, (b) Russian Sukhoi PAK FA and (c) Russian Su-35S fighter aircraft.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63214","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Lightning II aircraft is specifically designed to operate in a contested environment. Regular simulator work and operational analysis is carried out to confirm the system's performance and operational test of the aircraft is planned to do the same. The air system currently meets or exceeds our requirements. I am withholding the level of detail requested as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201935 ; 201971 ; 202105","2014-06-26T13:42:45.1557125Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63214/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63214/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the Lightning II's combat capability against the Russian (a) NNIIRT 55Zh6M Nebo Mobile and (b) Almaz-Antey S-400 / SA-21 Growler SAM System radar systems.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63215","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Lightning II aircraft is specifically designed to operate in a contested environment. Regular simulator work and operational analysis is carried out to confirm the system's performance and operational test of the aircraft is planned to do the same. The air system currently meets or exceeds our requirements. I am withholding the level of detail requested as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201935 ; 201936 ; 201971","2014-06-26T13:42:45.4142517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63215/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63215/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the loss/exchange ratio for the Lightning II is.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","202105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63216","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-10","<p>Expenditure on redundancy payments is not recorded separately by individual arms of service. However, the total of expenditure incurred on Military redundancy payments has been as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Total Redundancy Payments (£million)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>110</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>140</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Figure for 2013-14 will be published in the Ministry of Defence's Annual Report and Accounts 2013-2014.</p><p> </p><p>While reduced recruiting and fewer extensions of service will account for some of the reductions arising from the 2010 Strategic Defence &amp; Security Review decision on the future size and shape of the Regular Armed Forces, a redundancy programme is needed to ensure the right balance of skills for the future is maintained across the rank structures. We are providing as much support as possible to those personnel being made redundant.</p><p> </p><p>We estimate that, by 2021-22, we will have achieved cumulative savings of some £23 billion as a result of reductions in military and civilian personnel and greater efficiency in the conduct of non-front line activities.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-10T16:23:37.3954582Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63216/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63216/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63216/answer/previousversion/7469","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Armed Forces: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on redundancy payments to (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) Royal Air Force personnel in each financial year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63217","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-01","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for Modern Slavery and Organised Crime (Karen Bradley) on 30 June 2014, (Official Report, column 376W).</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-07-01T16:34:05.9401339Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63217/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63217/answer","20140630 Hansard extract on Interception Warrants.doc","20140630 Hansard extract on Interception Warrants.doc","20140630 Hansard extract on Interception warrants","20140630 Hansard extract on Interception warrants","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63217/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Interception Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many interception warrants were (a) issued, (b) declined and (c) cancelled by his Department under (i) section 8(1) and (ii) section 8(4) of the Regulation of Investigatory Powers Act 2000 in the last six months for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Sanders","Torbay","Mr Adrian Sanders","201669"
