="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/314795/uk_reserve_force_cadets_2014.pdf" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/314795/uk_reserve_force_cadets_2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/314795/uk_reserve_force_cadets_2014.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-07-01T16:54:31.279817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63218/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63218/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many sponsored reserves there were in the (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) Royal Air Force service in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63219","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-25","<p>Since January 2011, as part of the Transparency Agenda, central Government Departments have been required to publish information about contracts they award on Contracts Finder. A copy of the Ministry of Defence contract with Capita for the Army Recruitment Partnering project can be found at:<br><br>Recruiting Partnering Contract, part one:<br>https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;noticeid=473310&amp;fs=true<br><br>Part two:<br>https://online.contractsfinder.businesslink.gov.uk/Common/View%20Notice.aspx?site=1000&amp;lang=en&amp;noticeid=473847&amp;fs=true</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-25T16:06:49.636891Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63219/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63219/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of his Department's contract with Capita in relation to the Army Recruitment Partnering project.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63220","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Lightning II aircraft is specifically designed to operate in a contested environment. Regular simulator work and operational analysis is carried out to confirm the system's performance and operational test of the aircraft is planned to do the same. The air system currently meets or exceeds our requirements. I am withholding the level of detail requested as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","201935 ; 201936 ; 202105","2014-06-26T13:42:45.320447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63220/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63220/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-23","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the extent to which overseas espionage has compromised the fighting ability of the Lightning II; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","201971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63221","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-26","<p>Turnout across the UK at the European Parliamentary Elections 2014 was 35.4%, slightly higher than 34.5% at the previous election in 2009.</p><p>The Government is committed to maximising electoral registration to help support the highest possible turnout in elections.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-06-26T15:15:21.8100678Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63221/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63221/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Voting Behaviour","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what assessment he has made of the proportion of people that voted in the most recent nationwide elections; and what steps he is taking to encourage more people to vote at future elections.","false","Biography information for Jim Sheridan","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Jim Sheridan","201720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63222","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-30","<p>I have been to Northern Ireland three times in an official capacity since taking office. I visited Belfast on 8 October 2010; Lough Erne on 18 June 2013; and, Derry-Londonderry on 21 June 2013.</p><p> </p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-06-30T16:25:36.6362351Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63222/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63222/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, how many times he has visited Northern Ireland in an official capacity since taking office.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63223","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-26","<p>Information on the costs of receptions I host is published under the Government's transparency rules. The costs of the reception at Admiralty House to celebrate the Tour de France will be published under these rules at: gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications. The Cabinet Office provides staff for all regular receptions.</p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-06-26T16:20:53.7124782Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63223/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63223/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, how much the recent reception at Admiralty House to celebrate the Tour de France cost; how this cost was met; and who provided the staff for this event.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","201745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63224","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-26","<p>All members of the All Party Parliamentary Group on the Tour de France were invited to the reception held to celebrate the Tour de France at Admiralty House on 18 June 2014.</p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-06-26T16:21:51.3894577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63224/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63224/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, which parliamentarians were invited to the reception held to celebrate the Tour de France at Admiralty House on 18 June 2014; and on what basis they were selected.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","201746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63225","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-26","<p>The invitation list was compiled based on advice from the Tour de France hub, Welcome to Yorkshire and from the All Party Parliamentary Group on the Tour de France. We do not routinely publish the full invitation lists for receptions. Details of the cost of receptions and number of attendees are published on a quarterly basis.</p><p> </p>","Sheffield, Hallam","Mr Nick Clegg",,"2014-06-26T16:22:43.1627072Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63225/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Clegg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63225/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if he will publish the invitation list for the reception held to celebrate the Tour de France at Admiralty House on 18 June 2014; and on what basis each such organisation was selected.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","201747"
