"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63381","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>The Civil Service fast stream programme, including opportunities to join the Northern Ireland Civil Service as a fast streamer, is promoted via the Civil Service fast stream website.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-26T12:16:15.0591174Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63381/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63381/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63381/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Civil Servants: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how the Northern Ireland Office promotes the Civil Service Fast Stream programme in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63382","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>My Department has not accepted any apprentices as part of this scheme since it started.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-26T12:23:26.0167273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63382/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63382/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Civil Servants: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many apprentices the Northern Ireland Office accepted as part of the Civil Service Fast Track Apprenticeship Scheme in each year since the scheme started.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63383","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>Neither I nor my officials have had any discussions about specific parade notifications with any member of the Parades Commission since the period referred to in the question.</p><p>Consideration of parades notifications is an operational matter for the Parades Commission, acting independently of the Government, in exercise of their powers under the Public Processions (NI) Act 1998. I play no role in that process.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-26T12:22:01.4358052Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63383/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63383/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Parades","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether her Department has discussed the consideration of any specific parade application with any member of the Parades Commission since January 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63384","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>Like other UK Government departments, the Northern Ireland Office faces a significant reduction in its budget – of 11.15% in 2015/16. My department has therefore requested that all of its Arms-Length Bodies provide an impact statement on the practical measures that might be taken to meet such a reduction. I have not yet made any decision in respect of the Commission's budget. I met the acting chair of the Commission last week.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-26T12:39:54.4202286Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63384/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63384/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what her policy is on the future funding of the Northern Ireland Human Rights Commission; and whether there has been any recent change in that policy.","false","Biography information for Naomi Long","Belfast East","Naomi Long","201778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63385","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>We continue to seek information on the use of the Royal Prerogative of Mercy (RPM) for the years 1987 to 1997 from Departments where relevant material might be held.</p><p>An overall review of Departmental records and information procedures is ongoing and will include an external review of records and information procedures.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-07-07T12:33:38.1923957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63385/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63385/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Prerogative of Mercy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, with reference to the Answer of 13 May 2014, Official Report, column 521W, on Prerogative of Mercy, what progress has been made on the review of historical records relating to the use of the Royal Prerogative of Mercy between 1987 and 1997.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63386","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>I have no plans at present to attend the International Festival for Business but I shall discuss the Festival when I next meet the Northern Ireland Minister for Enterprise, Trade &amp; Investment.</p><p>I expect my Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland to discuss the Festival with the Chief Executive of UKTI when she meets him shortly.</p><p> </p>","South Leicestershire","Mr Andrew Robathan",,"2014-06-26T12:28:44.3046814Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63386/answer","Biography information for Lord Robathan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63386/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-23","Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to the Answer of 19 June 2014, Official Report, column 723, on business, whether the Minister of State for Northern Ireland plans to attend any of the 16 events planned by UK Trade & Investment in connection with the International Festival for Business in Liverpool.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63387","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-26","<p>Planning for the commemoration, in 2015, of the 200th anniversary of the Battle of Waterloo is being carried out by Waterloo 200, an umbrella organisation which is overseeing the anniversary. More information can be found on its website at the following link: www.waterloo200.org. In the June 2013 budget, the Chancellor announced funding circa £1m will be allocated to restore the site of the battle.</p><p>The previous Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, Maria Miller, was also pleased to announce in October 2013 that at least £10m will be made available by the Heritage Lottery Fund over the next four years to fund projects marking some of the UK's most important anniversaries and commemorative events, including the bicentenary of the Battle of Waterloo.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-06-26T15:18:50.5836862Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63387/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63387/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-23","Battle of Waterloo: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans the Government has to commemorate the bicentenary of the Battle of Waterloo.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","201741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63388","Prime Minister","false","2014-06-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 1 May 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, column 761W.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-06-26T09:30:04.0528337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63388/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63388/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-06-23","Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many times he has met with the Deputy First Minister of Northern Ireland in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","201731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63389","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport has contracted a premium payable to government of £433million over the course of the directly awarded passenger rail franchise to West Coast Trains Limited. In addition, the contract includes a provision which will trigger higher premiums to government if GDP growth is higher than forecast and lower premiums if GDP growth is lower than forecast (subject to minimum levels of movements in GDP from forecast). Notice must be provided to West Coast Trains Limited no later than 31 December 2016 of any intention to exercise the up to one year franchise extension.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:22:28.8864647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63389/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63389/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what total financial support from the public purse will be given to West Coast Trains Ltd for the duration of the directly awarded passenger rail franchise announced on 19 June 2014; and what the deadline is for exercising the optional one-year franchise extension from April 2017 to April 2018.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63390","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The core InterCity West Coast Direct Award Team numbered four officials, some of whom spent part of their time on other projects. The core team was supported by finance, legal, technical and economic specialists and received input from officials across the Department for Transport's Rail Executive and wider Department where appropriate.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:23:40.0821491Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63390/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63390/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many officials in his Department were involved in the negotiations with Virgin for the rail passenger franchise directly awarded to West Coast Trains Ltd.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63391","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport ran a procurement for legal, technical and financial advisers for the InterCity West Coast Direct Award project. The advisers contracted, and the estimated fees to be paid for the work on the project, are shown below:</p><p> </p><p>Legal advisers – Addleshaw Goddard - £204,960</p><p>Technical advisers – TRL-Halcrow - £227,607</p><p>Financial advisers – PwC - £264,467</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:25:09.5399606Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63391/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63391/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which external consultants were involved in the negotiations with Virgin for the rail passenger franchise directly awarded to West Coast Trains Ltd; and what the cost to his Department was of each such consultancy.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63392","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>I am not aware of any discussions at the Rail Delivery Group on an &quot;infrastructure alliance&quot; between West Coast Trains Limited and Network Rail.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:44:30.5687802Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63392/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63392/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Rail Delivery Group has discussed the infrastructure alliance planned between West Coast Trains (WCT) Ltd and Network Rail as part of the franchise directly awarded to WCT Ltd on 19 June 2014.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","201735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63393","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The agreed targets are contained within the Franchise Agreement between West Coast Trains Limited and the Secretary of State for Transport, which will be published in due course. The contract will be managed and enforced by officials in the Department for Transport.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:20:29.1784328Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63393/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63393/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his Department's targets for (a) punctuality, (b) passenger satisfaction and (c) cleanliness are in the rail passenger franchise awarded to West Coast Trains Ltd; when he expects these targets to be introduced on the franchise; and who will be responsible for regulating the franchisee's performance against each such target.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63394","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The core InterCity West Coast Direct Award Team numbered four officials, some of whom spent part of their time on other projects. The core team was supported by finance, legal, technical and economic specialists and received input from officials across the Department for Transport's Rail Executive and wider Department where appropriate.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:26:16.8331658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63394/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63394/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many officials in his Department were involved in the design of the rail passenger franchise directly awarded to West Coast Trains Ltd.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63395","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The specifications for both the Northern and TransPennine franchises have not yet been decided. A public consultation exercise is being conducted, which will inform these specifications. The consultation can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-northern-and-transpennine-express-rail-franchises" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-northern-and-transpennine-express-rail-franchises</a></p><p /> <p>.</p><p /> <p> </p><p />","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T14:34:01.9820958Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63395/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63395/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63395/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which stations with ticket offices on the (a) TransPennine and (b) Northern rail lines are likely to have their opening hours reduced as a result of the current re-franchising exercise.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","201785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63396","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>All passenger rolling stock is capable of being modified to modern access standards. Indeed,following consultation with its disability advisors, the Department for Transport has set out for the industry the work that must be completed to enable each fleet to operate after 2019. Whether to make that investment is a decision for the vehicle owners along with the bidders for the future Northern and TransPennine franchises, noting that some of the current fleet is expected to be displaced by electric units as a result of the Government's extensive programme of electrification in Northern England.</p><p> </p><p>The whole of the TransPennine fleet already meets current access standards, as does nine per cent of the Northern fleet. Work to make a further 36 per cent of Northern's vehicles fully accessible formed part of the recent directly awarded franchise agreement.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:29:44.6741665Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63396/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63396/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63396/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the current fleet of rolling stock operated by the franchise holders on the (a) TransPennine and (b) Northern lines will have to be replaced by 2020 as they are not compliant with existing legal standards on passenger accessibility.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","201787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63397","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>The specifications for both the Northern and TransPennine franchises have not yet been decided. A public consultation exercise is being conducted, which will inform these specifications. The consultation can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-northern-and-transpennine-express-rail-franchises" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-of-northern-and-transpennine-express-rail-franchises</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T14:35:36.1162031Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63397/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63397/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63397/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what minimum train service levels will be contained in the new franchises for rail passenger services on the (a) TransPennine and (b) Northern lines.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","201788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63398","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-30","<p> </p><p>Staffing levels are a commercial matter for Virgin Trains. The Department has not engaged with trades unions representing staff working on the West Coast Main Line regarding the franchise specification of the recent direct award to West Coast Trains Limited.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-30T11:16:37.6191094Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63398/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63398/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63398/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-23","West Coast Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the effect of the specifications in the rail passenger franchise directly awarded to West Coast Trains Ltd on 19 June 2014 on levels of (a) on-train, (b) station and (c) ticket office staffing; and what discussions on the franchise specifications (i) his Department and (ii) Virgin Trains has had with trades unions representing staff working on the West Coast Main Line.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","201757"
