"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63078","Department of Health","false","2014-06-30","<p>The following table provides the annual population of student midwives from 2011-12 to 2013-14. The table includes students enrolled on the degree and 18 month diploma courses.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2013-14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Midwife population</p></td><td><p>5,955</p></td><td><p>6,315</p></td><td><p>6,413</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><em>Source: </em>multi professional education and training budget monitoring returns</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-30T16:05:51.2024831Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63078/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/63078/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-20","Midwives","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the total number of student midwives has been in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","201616"
