vists can obtain DMS mental health treatment through the Veterans and Reserves Mental Health Programme. Implementation of the new measures started in April 2014.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","201505 ; 201506","2014-06-24T14:56:42.6666231Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62875/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62875/answer","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014.doc","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014.doc","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62875/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-19","Army Reserve","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department takes to ensure that members of the Army Reserve who are injured receive appropriate support.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","201504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62876","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>On current plans, all Type 26 Global Combat Ships will have the same base level of capability but equipment fits tailored to task will enable them to meet their specific operational requirements.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-26T13:44:14.3529124Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62876/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62876/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-19","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many variants of the Type 26 global combat ship are being planned.","false","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","201541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62877","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 17 March 2014, (Official Report, column 504W).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-25T16:07:54.786557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62877/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62877/answer","20140317 - Hansard Extract Type 26 Frigates.doc","20140317 - Hansard Extract Type 26 Frigates.doc","20140317 - Hansard extract","20140317 - Hansard extract","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62877/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-19","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the key stages of decision-making are in the procurement process of the Type 26 global combat ship.","false","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","201542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62878","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-26","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 3 December 2012 (Official Report, column 615W) to the hon. Member for Portsmouth North (Penny Mordaunt).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-26T13:43:32.6805749Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62878/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62878/answer","Hansard Extract 3 December 2012. 201543.doc","Hansard Extract 3 December 2012. 201543.doc","Hansard Extract 3 December 2013.","Hansard Extract 3 December 2013.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62878/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-19","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many countries have expressed in an interest in operating the Type 26 global combat ship.","false","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","201543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62879","Department for Education","false","2014-06-26","<p>All schools have a legal responsibility to provide a safe and secure environment. Under health and safety legislation, schools are required to conduct a health and safety risk assessment and put in place an appropriate policy to ensure that staff and pupils are not exposed to risks. This applies to activities on or off the school premises.</p><p>Schools are also required to undertake a range of employment and criminal record checks when making appointments and supervise visitors to the school building. Guidance is made available to schools to help them meet these legal requirements.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-06-26T16:05:24.5961587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62879/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62879/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-19","Pupils: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps he is taking to ensure that primary school children are safe inside the school building and in the surrounding area.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","201537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62880","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-26","<p>The Planning Act 2008 defines what can be included in an application for development consent for a nationally significant infrastructure project (NSIP). Electricity substations are not categorised as NSIPs in their own right but, under the Act, can be included in an application for development consent for such a project if they can be considered as associated development in England.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, substations may be included in applications for generating stations (including onshore wind farms) under the Act if they are integral to the main development.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-26T15:04:55.5184057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62880/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62880/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 11 June 2014, Official Report, column 167W, on wind power: electrical substations, what constitutes a nationally significant infrastructure proposal (a) generally and (b) in relation to onshore wind farms.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","201521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62881","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Development consent was granted in May 2013 for the Galloper project. The commercial viability of the Galloper project is a matter for the developers.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:50:02.9575056Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62881/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62881/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Wind Power: Suffolk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the future viability of the Galloper offshore wind farm project.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","201494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62882","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>The figures set out below are for gas grid connections that fall under the eight gas distribution networks in Great Britain. These figures do not include gas transmission, nor do they include Independent Gas Transporters (IGTs) as IGTs are not regulated (they are part of a relative price control as part of Ofgem's remit).</p><p>Please see figures below from 1 April 2012 until 31 March 2013:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td colspan="5"><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>New Housing</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Existing Housing</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Industrial/<br> commercial</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Fuel Poor</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>East of England</strong></p></td><td><p>1559</p></td><td><p>4534</p></td><td><p>74</p></td><td><p>2748</p></td><td><p><strong>8915</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>London</strong></p></td><td><p>635</p></td><td><p>1145</p></td><td><p>68</p></td><td><p>200</p></td><td><p><strong>2048</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>North West</strong></p></td><td><p>494</p></td><td><p>1523</p></td><td><p>57</p></td><td><p>1943</p></td><td><p><strong>4017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>West Midlands</strong></p></td><td><p>469</p></td><td><p>1257</p></td><td><p>47</p></td><td><p>1206</p></td><td><p><strong>2979</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Northern Gas Networks</strong></p></td><td><p>1187</p></td><td><p>3341</p></td><td><p>407</p></td><td><p>914</p></td><td><p><strong>5849</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Scotland</strong></p></td><td><p>378</p></td><td><p>7531</p></td><td><p>295</p></td><td><p>2801</p></td><td><p><strong>11005</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Southern</strong></p></td><td><p>3405</p></td><td><p>6577</p></td><td><p>458</p></td><td><p>120</p></td><td><p><strong>10560</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Wales &amp; West</strong></p></td><td><p>2653</p></td><td><p>5069</p></td><td><p>556</p></td><td><p>2105</p></td><td><p><strong>10383</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Industry</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>10780</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>30977</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1962</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>12037</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>55756</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Ofgem receive the 2013-14 regulatory year submissions from the companies on 31 July. We therefore do not have any more up-to-date information at the moment for gas distribution connections in 2014.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T14:59:40.3130784Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62882/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62882/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many properties were connected to the gas distribution network in (a) 2013 and (b) 2014.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","201495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62883","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-26","<p>The reasons for introducing competition for Contracts for Difference earlier than previously proposed are the potential to improve value for money (including by managing expenditure within the Levy Control Framework cap) and drive innovation; and because the strong development of the renewables pipeline has helped to create appropriate conditions for competition. In developing our proposals we have also been mindful of the final EU Guidelines on State aid for environmental protection and energy 2014-20 published on 9 April 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-26T15:05:36.8742772Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62883/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62883/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, which levy control framework constraints that have required him to move an early administrative allocation model for Contract for Difference auctions to an auction arrangement.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62884","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>The supply of propane gas in bulk and cylinder form is subject to UK competition law under the Competition and Markets Authority; and Health and Safety Regulations.</p><p>The study by the Office of Fair Trading into the off-grid energy market in 2011 showed that on the whole competition works well, with consumers offered a good choice of suppliers, and that the off-grid sector does not need price regulation.</p><p>Health and Safety Regulations place obligations on propane gas suppliers so that the supplier must ensure that the installation is safe to receive propane gas before refilling, that the product is safely contained and that the installation is fitted with a pressure regulator and other key safety devices.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:52:53.5878795Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62884/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62884/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Liquefied Petroleum Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of existing regulations on commercial propane gas providers.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","201530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62885","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>We anticipate that some generators will seek to establish the terms of any PPA and financing arrangements before they participate in the CfD allocation round, in order to understand better their likely costs. Such conditional PPAs could take a number of forms, from indicative terms to a signed contract.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:55:32.3619541Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62885/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62885/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether he expects independent low carbon generators to have secured conditional power purchase agreements prior to bidding in the Contract for Difference auction in October 2014.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62886","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The supply of LPG is subject to UK competition law under the Competition and Markets Authority.</p><p>The study by the Office of Fair Trading (OFT) into the off-grid energy market, published in October 2011, found that there is a generally positive initial impact of the Competition Commission (CC) Orders from 2009 to make it easier for consumers to switch Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) supplier.</p><p>In April 2012, the OFT also secured voluntary agreements from the major LPG suppliers to make changes to their domestic bulk customer contracts and improve transparency around switching and cancellation rights. These changes apply for both individual tank and metered estate customers.</p><p>The Competition and Markets Authority will continue to keep the Orders under review.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:52:24.6107493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62886/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62886/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Liquefied Petroleum Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what consumer protection is available for users of metered LPG users; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","201531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62887","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The Government is committed to a public consultation on the regulations on minimum standards of efficiency in the private rental sector. The Government expects to begin consultation shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:53:15.2265295Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62887/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62887/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Private Rented Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when his Department will start a public consultation on the regulations on minimum standards of efficiency in the private rental sector and section 43 of the Energy Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201557"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62888","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The Government will be in a position to bring forward secondary regulations on minimum standards of energy efficiency in the private rented sector once a consultation on the regulations has been published and responded to.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:52:53.1100105Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62888/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62888/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Private Rented Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when his Department will bring forward secondary regulations on minimum standards of energy efficiency in the private rented sector under section 43 of the Energy Act 2011.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62889","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-26","<p>In order to make a fair comparison between the RO and CfD, my officials have looked at the differences in support costs between the two support mechanisms over the full support period (20 years for the RO, 15 years for CfDs) for solar and biomass CHP.</p><p>The Government also supports biomass conversions under both the RO and CfDs. Given that the Government support for biomass conversion ends on 1<sup>st</sup> April 2027, support costs for biomass conversions have been modelled over 11 years (from 2016/17).</p><p><strong>Table 1: Comparison of Total Discounted RO and CfD Support Costs</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>£2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Renewables Obligation (RO) (20 yrs)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Contracts for Difference (CfDs) (15 yrs)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1GW of Solar PV (&gt;5MW)</p></td><td><p>£772m</p></td><td><p>£529m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1GW of Biomass CHP</p></td><td><p>£7,147m</p></td><td><p>£5,154m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>£2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Renewables Obligation (RO) (11 yrs)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Contracts for Difference (CfDs) (11 yrs)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1GW of Biomass Conversions</p></td><td><p>£2,620m</p></td><td><p>£2,325m</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em>*Estimates based on new capacity commissioning in financial year 2016/17. Values are in £2012 real prices and discounted to the first year of generation (2016/17), using the Government's 3.5% discount rate.</em></p><p>It is not possible to directly compare renewables support costs (offered via the Renewables Obligation and Contracts for Difference), with support costs offered via the capacity market, as support under the Capacity Market is offered only for capacity and does not vary directly with the amount of generation produced by a plant.</p><p>Under the Capacity Market, all successful capacity will receive the clearing price of the auction in which they bid. The first capacity market delivery year is in 2018/19. Our latest estimate of the average clearing price over the first 15 years of the Capacity Market is £34/kW/year (in 2012 prices). For 1GW of de-rated capacity this corresponds to £500m over 15 years.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-26T15:15:27.4119019Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62889/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62889/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the support cost over 15 years of (a) 1gw of field solar generating capacity procured with renewable obligation certificate or Contract for Difference support, (b) 1gw of biomass generating capacity procured with renewable obligation certificate or Contract for Difference support and (c) 1gw of gas fired power station capacity procured with capacity market payment support.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62890","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>We anticipate that some generators will seek to establish the terms of any PPA and financing arrangements before they participate in the CfD allocation round, in order to understand better their likely costs. Agreements between generators and PPA providers could take a number of different forms, from indicative terms to a signed contract. The decision to sign a conditional PPA ahead of the auction, and the duration of any agreement, are ultimately commercial matters.</p><p>We anticipate that the Offtaker of Last Resort (OLR) will encourage competition in the PPA market both at the outset of the CfD and once any initial PPA has expired. Generators agreeing to a conditional PPA would be able to participate in the later short-term PPA market, once their initial PPA had expired; backed by the protections afforded by the OLR.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T13:53:42.8961766Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62890/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62890/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether independent generators who sign a conditional power purchase agreement ahead of competing in a Contract for Difference auction will be able to participate in a later short-term power purchase market that the offtaker of last resort arrangements seek to support.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","201411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62891","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has not received any recent direct representations from industry regarding the effect of load management on performance and industry.</p><p>National Grid recently announced two new balancing services to balance supply and demand in the coming winters. One of these, Demand Side Balancing Reserve (DSBR), will extend existing arrangements for companies to receive payment to reduce their electricity use or switch to on-site generators for short periods when instructed by National Grid.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T15:46:27.9747434Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62891/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62891/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Land Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent representations he has received from industry on the effect of the use of land management measures on performance and productivity.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","201452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62892","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-25","<p>In 2012, it is estimated that there were approximately 2.83 million households in Great Britain that did not have access to the gas network; 2.21 million of these households were in England, 0.44 million in Scotland and 0.20 million in Wales.</p><p>Data on gas connections in Northern Ireland, and data on the number of households within 500 meters of the gas grid, are not held by DECC.</p><p>These data are available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sub-national-estimates-of-households-not-connected-to-the-gas-network" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sub-national-estimates-of-households-not-connected-to-the-gas-network</a>.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-25T11:24:46.4521674Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62892/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62892/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many households in (a) the UK, (b) England, (c) Scotland, (d) Wales and (e) Northern Ireland are off the mains gas grid.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","201492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62893","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p><strong>I have not held discussions with RWE or SSE on this issue because this is a commercial matter for the parties concerned.</strong></p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T15:49:37.9642453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62893/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62893/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Wind Power: Suffolk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions he has had with RWE and SSE concerning a replacement partner for the development of the Galloper offshore wind farm project.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","201491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62894","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-26","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 25 June 2014, <em>Official Report, Column 235-6W</em>.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-26T15:11:20.5912653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62894/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62894/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-19","Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of off-grid households in (a) the UK, (b) England, (c) Scotland, (d) Wales and (e) Northern Ireland are located within 500 metres of the gas grid.","false","Biography information for Tom Greatrex","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Tom Greatrex","201481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62895","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>As independent charities, handling correspondence is entirely a matter for the Canal &amp; River Trust and other similar trusts. However, I have asked my officials to draw this issue to the attention of the Trust at their next meeting.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-24T10:09:29.5520345Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62895/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62895/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will issue guidance to the West Midlands Waterways, Canal and River Trust and other similar trusts that replies to hon. Members who have written on behalf of their constituents should be signed.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","201453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62896","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>Core Defra provides three telephones lines with the prefix 0845 operated under contract by an external provider. Alternative numbers charged at BT local rates, using the prefix 0345, are available for all three lines and are the primary numbers. 0845 prefix numbers have been retained in order to minimise disruption to users during the transition to 0345 prefixed lines.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of calls each number has received in the last 12 months will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","North Cornwall","Dan Rogerson",,"2014-06-24T10:13:46.1011642Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62896/answer","Biography information for Dan Rogerson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62896/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-06-19","Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many telephone lines with the prefix (a) 0845, (b) 0844 and (c) 0843 his Department (i) operates and (ii) sponsors; how many calls each such number has received in the last 12 months; and whether alternative numbers charged at BT local rates are available in each such case.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","201442"
